    • Method Detail

      • add

        public javax.swing.JMenuItem add(javax.swing.Action action,
                                 java.lang.String tooltip)
        Add an action to this menu and return the menu item created. If the tool tip is null, use the "tooltip" property already in the action, otherwise add the property to the action. The new menu item is added to the action as the "menuItem" property. The menu item's text is set using the action's name and is enabled by default.

      • add

        public javax.swing.JMenuItem add(javax.swing.Action action,
                                 java.lang.String tooltip,
                                 java.lang.String label,
                                 boolean isEnabled)
        Add an action to the given menu and return the menu item created. If the tool tip is null, use the "tooltip" property already in the action, otherwise add the property to the action. The new menu item is added to the action as the "menuItem" property. The menu item's text is set to be "label", and is disabled or enabled according to "isEnabled."

        public java.lang.Object getTarget()
        The object that this context menu was created on.
